import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    genus_counts = data['Genus'].value_counts()
    genus_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Genus')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bacteria based on their genus?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot_data = data.groupby('Gram_Staining')['Neomycin'].apply(list)
    plt.boxplot(box_plot_data, labels=box_plot_data.index)
    plt.xlabel('Gram Staining')
    plt.ylabel('Neomycin')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Neomycin across different Gram Staining types?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
